<topic template="Default" status="Under Construction" lasteditedby="Adam" version="2" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title>Indexer</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table styleclass="PopupTable" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">An <text styleclass="VariableName-small">Indexer</text> is a cam device that is pre-assembled with an input and output shaft. When the input-shaft (cam) rotates continuously, the output-shaft &#160; moves, in steps, in one direction. The <text style="font-style:italic;">&apos;index&apos;</text> motion is also called a <text style="font-style:italic;">&apos;progressive&apos;</text> motion.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box">The output-shaft rotates progressively, in one direction, with a series of identical motions. After a number of index motions, the output-shaft rotates returns to its original position. </para>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="VariableName-small">Some definitions used with Indexers:</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">NUMBER-OF-STOPS</text>: The number of times the input shaft must rotate to index the output shaft one complete cycle. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">INDEX PERIOD</text>: The rotation, in degrees, of the input shaft to complete the <text styleclass="Popup Box2">INDEX</text>.</para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">DWELL PERIOD</text>: The rotation, in degrees, of the input shaft to complete the DWELL. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box2">INDEX PERIOD + DWELL PERIOD = 360. </para>
          <para styleclass="Popup Box"><text styleclass="Popup Box2">TYPE: 1, 2, 3:</text> number of <text styleclass="Popup Box2">INDEX-PERIODS</text> as the Input Shaft rotates once.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
  </body>
</topic>
